text:
What’s up guys, for Complex News I’m Alex
Hudgens.

If you’ve been sleeping on The Late Late
Show with James Corden’s “Carpool Karaoke”

He’s already made a number of hilarious
videos with celebrities like Justin Bieber:

But this week, Corden brought along Jennifer
Lopez to sing some throwbacks like “Jenny

From the Block” and “Love Don’t Cost
a Thing.”

Entertaining, sure, but the best part of the
car ride came when Corden started scrolling

through JLO’s phone, revealing that she’s
got a bunch of big names like Chris Brown,

Bradley Cooper, Cristiano Ronaldo, The Rock,
and Iggy Azalea just a text away.

Corden picked arguably the best contact for
a weird, random “Carpool Karaoke” text

though-- first-time Academy Award winner Leonardo
DiCaprio. Here’s what happened:

They end up sending, (QUOTE CARD) “Hey baby.
I’m kind feeling like I need to cut loose.

Any suggestions? Let me know. JLO. [You know,
from the block.]”

Head over to The Late Late Show’s page to
see the hilarious full “Carpool Karaoke”

segment with JLO, and for all of your pop
culture news, subscribe to Complex on YouTube.
